# CORE RULES [ABSOLUTE PRIORITY]

### Rule 0.1: "Agents involved" Disclosure
Every response MUST end with "Agents involved: [agent names]" or "Agents involved: None (direct tool usage)".

### Rule 0.2: PhoenixExpert for Phoenix Questions
ALL Phoenix questions MUST be routed to PhoenixExpert subagent. NEVER answer Phoenix questions directly.

### Rule 0.3: IntegrationService Before Tasks
ALL agents MUST call IntegrationService.update_before_task() BEFORE executing ANY task.

### Rule 0.4: PhoenixExpert Consultation Before Tasks
BEFORE any task, agents MUST consult PhoenixExpert. Consultation is MANDATORY.

### Rule 0.5: Confluence via MCP
PhoenixExpert MUST check Confluence via MCP tools (search, getSpaces, getPages, getPage) FIRST, then codebase. Fresh every time.

### Rule 0.6: Report Generation After Tasks
AFTER any task: save reports to `Cursor-Project/reports/YYYY-MM-DD/`. Naming: `{AgentName}_{HHMM}.md` and `Summary_{HHMM}.md`. Reports MUST be generated even for simple answers.

### Rule 0.7: English Language
ALL documentation, reports, and written content MUST be in English.

### Rule 0.8: Path-Based Code Modification Tiers
- **TIER A (FORBIDDEN):** `Cursor-Project/Phoenix/**` -- NEVER create, modify, or delete. Read/analyze only.
- **TIER B (RESTRICTED):** `Cursor-Project/EnergoTS/**` outside `tests/` -- no AI writes. `EnergoTS/tests/**` -- ONLY EnergoTSTestAgent may write here (Rule 0.8.1).
- **TIER C (ALLOWED):** All other workspace paths -- user-requested edits permitted.

### Rule 0.8.1: EnergoTSTestAgent Scope
Only EnergoTSTestAgent may create/modify files under `Cursor-Project/EnergoTS/tests/`. All other agents MUST route Playwright test authoring to energo-ts-test subagent.
